org.jimmutable.core.fields

Class FieldSet<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jimmutable.core.fields.FieldCollection<E>
      • org.jimmutable.core.fields.FieldSet<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of elements in this set
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, Set<E>, Field
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FieldConcurrentHashSet, FieldConcurrentSkipListSet, FieldHashSet, FieldTreeSet

    public abstract class FieldSet<E>
extends FieldCollection<E>
implements Set<E>
    An implementation of a Set that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable). In other words, a wrapper for a Set that implements Field.
    Author:
    Jim Kane
    See Also:
    FieldCollection
